From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 10:45:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: rockchip: Add bus-scan-delay-ms support

Armbian's working Rock Pi 4A 6.1.63 image carries a Rockchip PCIe host
patch that reads `bus-scan-delay-ms` from the device tree and sleeps
before scanning the PCI bus.  Its working boot log shows:

  rockchip-pcie f8000000.pcie: wait 1500 ms (from device tree) before bus scan

Port that behaviour to the modern Rockchip PCIe host driver so the Rock
Pi 4 DTS alignment patch can have the same effect.

This delay happens after link training and before PCI enumeration.  It is
not expected to fix an LTSSM/link-training timeout by itself, but it gives
us parity with the known-good Armbian kernel once the link comes up.
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c      |  4 ++++
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.h      |  2 ++
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c |  9 ++++++++-
 3 files changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
@@ -928,6 +928,7 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	struct device *dev = &pdev->dev;
 	struct pci_host_bridge *bridge;
-	int err;
+	int err;
+	u32 delay;
 
 	if (!dev->of_node)
 		return -ENODEV;
@@ -978,6 +979,13 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	bridge->sysdata = rockchip;
 	bridge->ops = &rockchip_pcie_ops;
 
+	delay = rockchip->bus_scan_delay;
+	if (delay > 0) {
+		dev_info(dev, "wait %u ms (from device tree) before bus scan\n",
+			 delay);
+		msleep(delay);
+	}
+
 	err = rockchip_pcie_setup_irq(rockchip);
 	if (err)
 		goto err_remove_irq_domain;
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c
@@ -100,6 +100,10 @@ int rockchip_pcie_parse_dt(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
 	if (rockchip->num_clks < 0)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, rockchip->num_clks,
 				     "failed to get clocks\n");
+
+	if (of_property_read_u32(node, "bus-scan-delay-ms",
+				 &rockchip->bus_scan_delay))
+		rockchip->bus_scan_delay = 0;
 
 	return 0;
 }
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.h
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.h
@@ -328,6 +328,8 @@ struct rockchip_pcie {
 	phys_addr_t msg_bus_addr;
 	bool is_rc;
 	struct resource *mem_res;
+	/* Delay in ms before PCI bus scan for slow endpoints. */
+	u32 bus_scan_delay;
 };
 
 static u32 rockchip_pcie_read(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip, u32 reg)
